  "prompt": "Do landlords actually call employers for background checks?",
  "response": "Yes, many landlords do contact employers as part of their background check process. Verifying employment is a way for landlords to ensure that potential tenants have a stable source of income and can afford the rent. In addition to checking employment status, landlords might also confirm salary details, job stability, and the likelihood of continued employment. However, the extent to which landlords perform these checks can vary. Some may rely on documentation provided by the tenant, such as pay stubs or letters of employment, while others may directly contact employers for confirmation.",
